HEADWORD: Turner
<hw>Turn"er</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧rn"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who turns; especially, one whose occupation is to form articles
with a lathe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A variety of pigeon; a
tumbler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turner</ent>⟦br⟧
